metadata.name: Try/Hatch #104
metadata.description:
In full screen view, click on the graphic to download plottable SVG in A3 format.

The color palette used in here is supposed to represent 25 Stabilo Point fineliners. The color values don't come from any official specification, though.

Every minted edition consists of 3 color layers:

- black-ish (pen number 46) with constant hatching distance
- two color layers with randomly chosen color and distance values

If you have a pen plotter, you can jump straight into making a physical drawing. Please be aware, that physical plot might differ from the digital version due to the pen and paper color differences.

Each group ID consists of an index, a HEX color value, and a Stabilo Point pen color number. In Inkscape, just convert groups to layers, and you can start to plot (probably the best experience with AxiDraw A3 pen plotter).

If you don't own a plotter or you want a regular print, simply convert your SVG to raster format.

metadata.name: Garden Of Symmetry #69
metadata.description:
Sometimes, things look better when seen from the distance. Not from far away, but from a length that allows one to see whatâ€™s possibly underneath. Or, you may not see anything. Instead, you can just enjoy things falling into place.

Get a pack of shattered glass, snow, or ice*, uncovering a pattern. Or an axis of dancing geometries. Enter the Garden of Symmetry.

The graphic is a plottable SVG file in A3 format, ready to be drawn using a pen plotter. In the full screen view, click somewhere on the artwork to download a copy.

I recommend to optimize the SVG before plotting, i.e. using vpype. I also recommend to draw the graphic using 0.7mm pen.

metadata.name: A Bugged Forest #896
metadata.description:
A forest has stories to tell.
About times that were, about times that will be.
-
This project was minted in much unusual conditions. 
We gathered here, by 38 degrees heat. We belong to a crowd who loves stories, of civilisations at stake and deities, of afterlife and worship. We drank and hugged and chanted pagan hymns. We minted the Bugged Forest from our place on earth that we call Hell just for the fun of it. We are passionate, and loving, and angry and desperate. We, people of the soil, under a bugged sun.
-
This project is the long-form version of an algorithm that contains a bug. â€œThe Bugged Treeâ€â€™s code was salvaged and stored and served as the core motivation and engine for an entire forest. Its concept is about releasing the control. I am a  byproduct of evolution, an iteration of that specie who wanted utter control, and which at some point, lost control over its own creation. As a generative artist, I chose to welcome the event of chance into my creative process. The symbolism in chance made me feel humble and free. Unwilling to make any change to a story that the Tree needed to tell me, as a listener, rather than a writer of my own idealised fantasies.
-
The iterations arenâ€™t under control. They may be odd and off. We have to accept it. They are also plottable, press [s] in live mode to get a SVG. Attempt the plot at your own risk, as thereâ€™s a possibility for it to come near to impossibilities or cause paper or motor damage, and most certainly, a bugged drawing.
-
From Earth or from Hell, with love, yours truthfully, NFTBiker and zancan
